yhadithonline\/2023\/07\/05\/not-hurting-others\/","url_meta":{"origin":1703,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Harm: Not hurting others is obligatory charity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 5, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Dharr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cRefrain from harming people, for it is your charity due upon yourself.\u201d Source: al-S\u0323amt li-Ibn Abi\u0304 Dunya\u0304 68 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0630\u064e\u0631\u064d\u0651 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064f\u0641\u064f\u0651 \u0634\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0651\u0643\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21173,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/11\/11\/graves-desecrating-dead\/","url_meta":{"origin":1703,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Graves: Desecrating the dead like harming the living","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 11, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cBreaking the bones of a dead person is like breaking them when he is alive.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 3207 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Nawawi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0631\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21067,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/10\/20\/harm-dog-pig-haqq-believers\/","url_meta":{"origin":1703,"position":2},"title":"Fudayl on Justice: No harming animals, how can you harm believers?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 20, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Dhahabi reported: Fudayl ibn 'Iyad, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cBy Allah, it is not lawful for you to harm a dog or a pig without a just cause, so how can you harm a Muslim?\u201d Source: Siyar A\u02bbla\u0304m al-Nubala\u0304\u02bc 8\/427 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0630\u0647\u0628\u064a \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0641\u064f\u0636\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0644\u064f \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":40618,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/07\/05\/harm-excluded\/","url_meta":{"origin":1703,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Najwa: Do not harm believers by excluding them","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 5, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cLet not two privately converse to the exclusion of a third, for that will hurt the believer and Allah Almighty hates for the believer to be hurt.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Awsat\u0323 lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 1986 Grade: Thiqah (reliable) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32279,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/18\/removing-harm-roads\/","url_meta":{"origin":1703,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Hasanat: Removing harm from roads leads to Paradise","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 18, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ma\u2019qil ibn Yasar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Whoever clears harmful things from the roads of the Muslims, a good deed will be recorded for him. Whoever is awarded a good deed, he will enter Paradise.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Kabi\u0304r lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 20\/216 Grade: Hasan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32128,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/15\/removing-harm-enjoining-good\/","url_meta":{"origin":1703,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Sadaqa: Removing harm, enjoining good are charity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The M